Office on July 20, 1981, the attached Amendment IV to the

Constitution and Bylaws of the Manchester Band of Pomo Indians of the

Manchester Rancheria of California, was submitted to the qualified voters 

of the tribe and was on September 12, 1981, duly adopted/rejeected by

a vote of 19 for, and 5 against, in an election in which at least

thirty percent (30%) of the 57 entitled to vote cast their ballots

in accordance with Section 16 of the Indian Reorganization Act of June 18, 

1934 (48 Stat. 984), as amended by the Act of June 15, 1935 (49 Stat. 378).

