AMENDMENT 

CONSTITUTION AND BYLAWS

OF THE 
MANCHESTER-POINT ARENA BAND OF POMO INDIANS 
OF THE MANCHESTER-POINT ARENA RANCHERIA 
CALIFORNIA

AMENDMENT V


Article III, Section 2 - GOVERNING BODY - shall be amended in 
its entirety to read as follows:

Section 2. All enrolled members who are 18 years of age 
or over, who have maintained legal residence on the 
Rancheria for a period of six (6) months. Residency 
shall be defined as residing 6 months on the Rancheria, 
prior to any election. Members who have established 
their 6 months residency would retain their residency 
voting rights, should they leave the Rancheria for any of 
the following reasons.

1.  Military duty.

2.  Full or part time students who are furthering their 
education.

3.  Vacations or extended vacations.

4.  To seek employment.

5.  Medical reasons.

6. Correctional facility.

Such residence, however, shall not be required as a 
qualification for voting upon amendments to the 
Constitution and attached Bylaws.

certificate of results of election

